<!-- LayoutDestination enumeration: "SelectedLayout" specifies layout by name from list; other values similar to Go to Layout step. -->
<!-- NewWndStyles attributes: DimParentWindow ("Yes" darkens layout area of parent window for card, "No" does not); Toolbars ("Yes" shows FileMaker Pro status toolbar and FileMaker Go toolbar/editing toolbar, "No" does not); MenuBar ("Yes" shows area at top displaying installed menu set, "No" does not; not supported in macOS or when active window is card); Style ("Document" opens document window; "FloatingDocument" opens floating document window; "Dialog" opens dialog window; "Card" opens card); Close ("Yes" enables close button in window's title bar, "No" does not); Minimize ("Yes" enables minimize button in window's title bar, "No" does not); Maximize ("Yes" enables maximize button in window's title bar, "No" does not); Resize ("Yes" allows users to resize window, "No" does not); Styles (numeric style flags). -->
<!-- NewWndStyles Style="Document | Floating | Dialog | Card" -->
<!-- Optional: LayoutDestination, Layout (layout to be used), Name (window name; does not have to be unique), Height (height of new window in points), Width (width of new window in points), DistanceFromTop (new window's distance in points from top of screen; or for card, from top of layout in parent window), DistanceFromLeft (new window's distance in points from left of screen; or for card, from left of parent window), NewWndStyles. -->
<!-- Creates new window based on foreground window. Can create document window, floating document window, dialog window, or card. -->
<!-- Not necessary to enter values for each option. When no value entered, FileMaker Pro uses default value associated with Window menu > New Window command. -->
<!-- When both maximize and minimize buttons disabled, these buttons do not appear in window's title bar. -->
<!-- Can use script or button script step to control window, even if window controls disabled in window's title bar. -->
<!-- FileMaker Go: does not support Floating Document and Dialog window style options; supports positioning and resizing options only for cards; always displays document windows in full screen. -->
<!-- Data API and CWP: do not support window style settings. -->
<!-- Partial support on Go (no Floating Document, Dialog; cards only for positioning/resizing; full screen documents), WebDirect (Document and Card only; one document + one card max; virtual windows), and CWP (no window style settings). -->
<!-- See https://help.claris.com/en/pro-help/content/new-window.html -->
